1
00:00:11,060 --> 00:00:19,220
Are you enjoying your morning so far? Did you get a special breakfast? No? Are you going to get special lunch? There you go.

2
00:00:20,390 --> 00:00:29,140
Well, may that be a wonderful time today. We're glad that you're here, and if you were a guest with us, we're just delighted that you would come and celebrate the Lord's Day with us today.

3
00:00:29,140 --> 00:00:40,720
We are in a series right now on Kingdom Living, asking the question, what does an authentic faith in Jesus really look like in a variety of dimensions of our life?

4
00:00:40,720 --> 00:00:47,060
And this morning, we come to this issue of what does it mean to be a Christian parent?

5
00:00:49,210 --> 00:00:52,710
Father's Day seemed like an appropriate day to look at this issue of parenting.

6
00:00:52,890 --> 00:00:59,370
So this actually is for both moms and dads, grandparents, parents-to-be-someday, grandparents-to-be-someday.

7
00:00:59,830 --> 00:01:02,690
You can extrapolate, and it covers all of us.

8
00:01:03,330 --> 00:01:09,520
Whether you mentor a child, a big brother, big sister, this is for you.

9
00:01:09,520 --> 00:01:15,940
And I hope you'll realize that you can be a Christian and be a parent.

10
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:19,360
And that's different from being a Christian parent.

11
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:22,580
And we're going to look at the difference this morning.

12
00:01:22,980 --> 00:01:28,280
And I want to challenge us and encourage us on what Christian parenting might look like.

13
00:01:30,950 --> 00:01:37,310
So whether you are a two-parent nuclear family, a single mom, a single father, or any other family arrangement,

14
00:01:37,310 --> 00:01:39,870
whether you're a dad, mom, grandparent

15
00:01:39,870 --> 00:01:42,990
or someday one or more of the above

16
00:01:42,990 --> 00:01:44,750
this is for you

17
00:01:44,750 --> 00:01:46,290
and we're glad that you're here

18
00:01:46,290 --> 00:01:47,150
and you can hear this

19
00:01:47,150 --> 00:01:47,810
and my prayer

20
00:01:47,810 --> 00:01:49,530
is that you'll be encouraged

21
00:01:49,530 --> 00:01:51,870
as you live out your faith in Christ

22
00:01:51,870 --> 00:01:54,290
to live it out in these experiences

23
00:01:54,290 --> 00:01:55,550
and that God will bless you

24
00:01:55,550 --> 00:01:57,530
as you mentor and parent

25
00:01:57,530 --> 00:01:59,330
today and in the future

26
00:01:59,330 --> 00:02:01,510
I'm indebted to this

27
00:02:01,510 --> 00:02:02,930
for this message

28
00:02:02,930 --> 00:02:03,790
much of the material

29
00:02:03,790 --> 00:02:05,670
coming out of a phenomenal article

30
00:02:05,670 --> 00:02:07,370
called Parenting

31
00:02:07,370 --> 00:02:11,190
in a great book called The Complete Book of Everyday Christianity

32
00:02:11,190 --> 00:02:13,610
by R. Paul Stevens and Robert Banks.

33
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:20,020
And so I share with you, what are we doing when we parent a child?

34
00:02:20,020 --> 00:02:27,840
What are we really doing when God gives us the privilege of a child in our lives?

35
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:29,820
And we say we are parenting.

36
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,200
What are we really doing?

37
00:02:33,410 --> 00:02:39,500
We're taking care of three things, body and soul and spirit.

38
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:48,120
we are nurturing a body and a soul and a spirit we're conceiving and caring for a little body we

39
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:55,690
are loving and nurturing a soul as their personality develops and their spirit we're

40
00:02:55,690 --> 00:03:02,520
pointing them to god and developing i hope a hunger for god and his word as we parent

41
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:09,590
body soul and spirit and that kind of relationship that experience of parenting

42
00:03:09,590 --> 00:03:16,780
changes and shapes both the children and the parents

43
00:03:16,780 --> 00:03:20,480
or the grandparents or whoever's caring.

44
00:03:21,330 --> 00:03:24,370
We often ask, well, how did the kids turn out after you're done?

45
00:03:26,450 --> 00:03:29,610
The question also is, how did the parents turn out?

46
00:03:30,660 --> 00:03:31,380
Are you different?

47
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:33,740
How did it exchange you?

48
00:03:34,180 --> 00:03:38,340
How did the experience of raising a little one grow you?

49
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:43,160
What did God do in you in that experience as well?

50
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:45,180
Friends, you are parenting.

51
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:47,740
You are forming a body and a soul and a spirit.

52
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:51,280
That couldn't be more important in this world.

53
00:03:52,660 --> 00:03:55,000
And sadly, though, some in our Western culture,

54
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:58,980
they see parenting, unfortunately, as kind of a nuisance,

55
00:03:59,990 --> 00:04:03,570
something that comes along, and it's nice to have the trophy children,

56
00:04:03,570 --> 00:04:05,950
but we've got other things to do.

57
00:04:08,030 --> 00:04:12,190
We look to our careers to find ourselves and be actualized.

58
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:16,900
James Dobson, the famous psychologist, says,

59
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:26,060
The average father in America spends less than a minute of face-to-face communication with his children per day.

60
00:04:27,970 --> 00:04:28,810
That's so sad.

61
00:04:30,540 --> 00:04:31,440
Oh, it's so sad.

62
00:04:32,690 --> 00:04:33,370
The average father.

63
00:04:33,630 --> 00:04:35,810
Christian parents do it differently.

64
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:41,920
With Jesus in our life, with the Holy Spirit coursing through us, we do it differently.

65
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:47,000
But you know what, that sentiment goes back a long ways too.

66
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:52,970
Socrates, in 470 B.C., somewhere way back in there, he said this,

67
00:04:52,970 --> 00:04:56,530
Could I climb to the highest place in Athens?

68
00:04:57,350 --> 00:04:59,690
I would lift my voice and proclaim,

69
00:05:00,210 --> 00:05:05,890
Fellow citizens, why do you turn and scrape every stone to gather wealth,

70
00:05:05,890 --> 00:05:10,010
and take so little care of your children

71
00:05:10,010 --> 00:05:14,250
to whom one day you must relinquish it all.

72
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:20,050
We've been struggling with this issue of time and energy and parenting

73
00:05:20,050 --> 00:05:21,890
for a long time.

74
00:05:23,790 --> 00:05:26,730
And I want us, as people living today,

75
00:05:27,070 --> 00:05:30,340
to really come to grips with this issue

76
00:05:30,340 --> 00:05:33,880
that we understand what real Christians do when they parent

77
00:05:33,880 --> 00:05:38,540
and how it's different than perhaps others in the world around us.

78
00:05:39,860 --> 00:05:40,920
First thing I want to say,

79
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:44,920
if you'll excuse me, I'm struggling with laryngitis.

80
00:05:46,070 --> 00:05:47,270
Brad, could you get me a cup of water?

81
00:05:47,430 --> 00:05:49,110
That would be so helpful at this moment

82
00:05:49,110 --> 00:05:50,830
before I have a tickle fest in my throat.

83
00:05:51,210 --> 00:05:51,830
You got one there?

84
00:05:52,270 --> 00:05:52,950
Thank the Lord.

85
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:57,690
Thank you, my friend.

86
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:00,560
I thought I could make it.

87
00:06:02,180 --> 00:06:02,860
It came close.

88
00:06:03,140 --> 00:06:03,980
Only second page.

89
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:08,400
Well, anyway.

90
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:14,400
Parenting, friends, is more than a job.

91
00:06:15,730 --> 00:06:18,010
Parenting is a vocation.

92
00:06:18,010 --> 00:06:20,160
Do you believe that?

93
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:32,210
parenting is a vocation a vocation is a calling a vocation is a summons by God on your life

94
00:06:32,210 --> 00:06:42,520
and parenting is a vocation because we're called by God to do it and it comes from God we're parents

95
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:48,460
because God allows us to be parents the whole idea of the parenting relationship comes from God

96
00:06:48,460 --> 00:06:57,210
genesis 1 27 so god created people in his own image and god patterned them after himself

97
00:06:57,210 --> 00:07:05,880
male and female he created them god blessed them and told them multiply and fill the earth

98
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:17,270
and subdue the earth god blesses god set up this relationship in parenting it's a high calling

99
00:07:19,010 --> 00:07:21,910
It's something that we do in partnership with God.

100
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:25,960
It's profound.

101
00:07:28,490 --> 00:07:29,510
Dobson again says,

102
00:07:29,510 --> 00:07:37,970
No job can compete with the responsibility of shaping and molding a new human being.

103
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:41,440
There's nothing like that on earth.

104
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:48,100
Our projects at work might be exciting, but there's nothing like shaping a life.

105
00:07:50,140 --> 00:07:51,900
It's a calling. It's a calling of God.

106
00:07:51,900 --> 00:08:03,490
If we think that that bonus for slaving away at the office is more important than shaping a life, we've missed it.

107
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:11,020
If we think that promotion is worth more than shaping the life that God has given us, we've missed it.

108
00:08:12,070 --> 00:08:14,030
There's nothing like parenting.

109
00:08:16,010 --> 00:08:17,050
I'll share a short story.

110
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:24,700
It's said of a gentleman by the name of Boswell who was the famous biographer to Samuel Johnson.

111
00:08:24,700 --> 00:08:31,680
There was a day that this gentleman referred to over and over as a special day in his childhood

112
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:37,970
when his father took him fishing out to a river or to a lake.

113
00:08:38,070 --> 00:08:39,330
You can imagine the scene.

114
00:08:40,450 --> 00:08:43,190
It was a day that in his adult mind was fixed,

115
00:08:43,630 --> 00:08:49,930
and he reflected on it how his father taught him so many wonderful things in that experience of fishing.

116
00:08:51,940 --> 00:08:55,120
And after people had heard so much about that fishing trip,

117
00:08:56,180 --> 00:09:06,100
Somebody else checked the journal of Boswell's father to see what he said about that special and amazing day.

118
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:11,560
And so when a friend turned to the journal, this is what it said.

119
00:09:13,340 --> 00:09:15,100
Gone fishing today with my son.

120
00:09:16,220 --> 00:09:17,060
A day wasted.

121
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:20,740
Isn't that sad?

122
00:09:23,910 --> 00:09:30,620
Think how a day in the life of a child can bless and affect a child.

123
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:40,840
think how a day focused on a child with you fully cognizant of the shaping you're doing how that can

124
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:49,610
impact a child parenting is a calling it's a vocation from god and there's nothing like it

125
00:09:49,610 --> 00:10:02,690
on earth men and women are you giving your parenting the appropriate time and energy

126
00:10:02,690 --> 00:10:08,620
if you're a grandparent and god has you deeply involved in the lives of your grandchildren

127
00:10:08,620 --> 00:10:12,510
Are you giving it the energy that God would have?

128
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:18,000
Or have you let the things of the world and the promotions and the other benefits

129
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:24,580
and the things that seem so important crowd out this vocation that God has called you to?

130
00:10:26,270 --> 00:10:32,020
Do you see your role as a parent, as a grandparent, as a vocation from God himself?

131
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:39,300
And if you don't, my prayer for you is that you begin to ask God that he would reveal that to you.

132
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:43,600
that you might grab it with all the gusto in which He has called you.

133
00:10:45,450 --> 00:10:47,010
Parenting is a vocation.

134
00:10:47,170 --> 00:10:50,200
Parenting, number two, is also stewardship.

135
00:10:52,220 --> 00:10:54,620
Because who really owns those children?

136
00:10:56,370 --> 00:10:57,230
It's not us.

137
00:10:59,060 --> 00:11:01,940
They're a gift from God, and God owns everything.

138
00:11:02,420 --> 00:11:04,600
The children are ultimately the Lord's.

139
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:06,760
We never really own them.

140
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:13,640
We have the privilege of blessing and pouring into their lives on God's behalf.

141
00:11:13,780 --> 00:11:27,080
psalm 127 says children are a gift from the lord they are a reward from him they were thought about

142
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:36,030
it but our children don't choose us and we really don't choose our children do we they're given

143
00:11:36,030 --> 00:11:44,840
they're entrusted to us for care for nurture the gifts that god has placed in them we are

144
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:55,580
entrusted to develop and to bring out on behalf of god the real owner of those children are we

145
00:11:55,580 --> 00:12:03,500
willing to give up those children to the lord the true owner we're there to shape and guide and

146
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:10,860
develop in whatever way we can god has hardwired them with gifts and spiritual gifts over time

147
00:12:12,140 --> 00:12:18,100
Our job is to grow it and to water it and to shape it and prune it and bless that child.

148
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:29,410
The funny thing is, you may be an engineer and God may have hardwired your child to be the artist.

149
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:32,890
And that's an interesting challenge, isn't it?

150
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:40,600
You may be a poet, but God has created your child to be an analyst.

151
00:12:41,220 --> 00:12:44,760
And that experience can be really unique.

152
00:12:44,760 --> 00:12:48,050
but God has entrusted us to develop

153
00:12:48,050 --> 00:12:51,070
and to bless and nurture that child

154
00:12:51,070 --> 00:12:53,630
not to replicate us

155
00:12:53,630 --> 00:12:57,830
but to develop all that God is doing in that child

156
00:12:57,830 --> 00:13:01,550
whether they look like us or follow our style

157
00:13:01,550 --> 00:13:04,530
or our vocation or our occupation or not

158
00:13:04,530 --> 00:13:08,600
I think sometimes we parents

159
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:10,500
we have these unfulfilled desires

160
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:12,280
from our own childhood

161
00:13:12,280 --> 00:13:15,060
and we want our children to somehow fulfill those

162
00:13:16,990 --> 00:13:19,850
We need to let them be who God made them to be.

163
00:13:21,380 --> 00:13:22,500
Because God is the owner.

164
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:25,340
We're there to nurture what God is doing in those children.

165
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:28,740
Do you see your children as gifts from God?

166
00:13:31,290 --> 00:13:35,880
Are you a faithful steward as you raise your children and grandchildren?

167
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:40,720
As you father and parent or mother and as you grandparent, as you mentor,

168
00:13:42,740 --> 00:13:43,740
do you see it as stewardship?

169
00:13:47,580 --> 00:13:52,600
Number three, parenting also is a form of ministering the gospel.

170
00:13:54,050 --> 00:13:58,930
It's been said this, that the best way for a child to learn to fear God

171
00:13:58,930 --> 00:14:02,470
is to know a real Christian.

172
00:14:03,860 --> 00:14:08,160
The best way for a child to learn to pray is to live with a father and a mother

173
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:12,810
who know a friendship with God and who truly pray.

174
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:19,800
Parenting is a way of ministering the gospel.

175
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:25,380
We want those children to know and come to know the Father as well.

176
00:14:25,380 --> 00:14:28,630
and we must be in a relationship with the Father

177
00:14:28,630 --> 00:14:31,410
that they might see the example in us.

178
00:14:33,670 --> 00:14:37,010
See, Christian parents, we live the life,

179
00:14:38,110 --> 00:14:41,070
we live the good news in our homes

180
00:14:41,070 --> 00:14:45,120
so that the children understand who God is

181
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:47,080
and begin to hunger for Him.

182
00:14:49,310 --> 00:14:51,770
And if we don't live it authentically at home,

183
00:14:53,060 --> 00:14:56,000
if we don't really live out the truths of the Gospel,

184
00:14:58,380 --> 00:15:00,740
they're not going to see an accurate reflection of God.

185
00:15:00,980 --> 00:15:08,440
See, the amazing thing is when the children are very little, they practically think we're God.

186
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:16,180
And how we treat them and how much grace and discipline and mercy and love we give them,

187
00:15:16,860 --> 00:15:20,020
they're forming their picture of the Heavenly Father through us.

188
00:15:24,660 --> 00:15:30,340
It's also been said you really understand the gospel when you can live it in the presence of your home.

189
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:34,570
It's one thing to be nice here.

190
00:15:34,990 --> 00:15:39,020
It's another thing to be nice in the parking lot after church, right?

191
00:15:39,240 --> 00:15:45,470
Boy, I've left church services and big, big churches in my other days,

192
00:15:45,610 --> 00:15:47,430
and we hear about mercy and love.

193
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:50,070
We get in the parking lot, and it's out of my way.

194
00:15:52,760 --> 00:15:54,500
Now you've got to get home.

195
00:15:54,700 --> 00:15:56,320
You're even further from the church service.

196
00:15:56,620 --> 00:16:04,570
Can you live out mercy and love and grace and patience at home Monday through Saturday?

197
00:16:08,030 --> 00:16:10,950
That's why we come back here every week to get filled up again,

198
00:16:10,950 --> 00:16:13,570
that we might live that out

199
00:16:13,570 --> 00:16:15,950
because we want our children, our grandchildren,

200
00:16:16,630 --> 00:16:19,510
those that we love and mentor to really see God

201
00:16:19,510 --> 00:16:23,760
through how we live authentically before Him.

202
00:16:28,650 --> 00:16:31,730
There was a survey of elementary children a few years ago,

203
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:36,920
and they indicated the ten most appreciated qualities for a dad.

204
00:16:38,930 --> 00:16:40,810
Number one, he takes time for me.

205
00:16:43,150 --> 00:16:44,810
Number two, he listens to me.

206
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:48,560
Number three, he plays with me.

207
00:16:50,790 --> 00:16:53,350
Therefore, he invites me to go places with him.

208
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:57,470
He lets me help him.

209
00:16:59,630 --> 00:17:01,030
He treats my mother well.

210
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:05,020
He lets me say what I think.

211
00:17:07,470 --> 00:17:09,270
He's nice to my friends.

212
00:17:11,760 --> 00:17:14,320
He only punishes me when I deserve it.

213
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:19,300
And he isn't afraid to admit when he's wrong.

214
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:23,920
That sounds like living out the gospel to me.

215
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:28,740
And that's what these children appreciated so much in their fathers.

216
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:33,280
The Bible says in Ephesians chapter 6,

217
00:17:33,280 --> 00:17:39,210
children obey your parents because you belong to the lord we've been looking at this passage

218
00:17:39,210 --> 00:17:46,680
for this is the right thing to do honor your father and your mother this is the first of the

219
00:17:46,680 --> 00:17:52,900
ten commandments that ends with a promise and here is the promise if you honor your father and mother

220
00:17:52,900 --> 00:18:00,680
you will live a long life full of blessing and now a word to you fathers don't make your children

221
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:04,880
angry by the way you treat them. Rather, bring them up

222
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:08,480
with the discipline and the instruction approved

223
00:18:08,480 --> 00:18:14,300
by the Lord. Discipline and instruction.

224
00:18:14,940 --> 00:18:18,000
Discipline and the word disciple

225
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:23,590
are closely related. The goal of the Christian discipline

226
00:18:23,590 --> 00:18:26,970
is to see our children grow into mature disciples

227
00:18:26,970 --> 00:18:31,860
of Jesus Christ. So we show them

228
00:18:31,860 --> 00:18:34,590
And we tell them what that means.

229
00:18:37,230 --> 00:18:44,480
We say, follow my example, as we parents follow the example of Jesus Christ.

230
00:18:44,940 --> 00:18:47,860
Paul wrote that in 1 Corinthians chapter 11.

231
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:50,880
That's for us, parents, grandparents.

232
00:18:51,540 --> 00:18:55,500
Follow my example, little ones, as I follow the example of Jesus.

233
00:18:55,820 --> 00:19:00,120
If we want them to follow Jesus, we've got to really live out the gospel,

234
00:19:00,580 --> 00:19:03,500
day in and day out, that we might say that with integrity.

235
00:19:07,370 --> 00:19:11,030
Part of parenting is teaching those children who God is.

236
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:19,570
The famous British poet Samuel Taylor Coleridge once had a discussion with a man

237
00:19:19,570 --> 00:19:25,220
that believed that children should not be given any formal religious education.

238
00:19:26,470 --> 00:19:28,130
That's in vogue today, by the way.

